  "calmGuideTitle": "When anger rises,\nlower your body safely first",
  "calmGuideSubtitle": "Fury Note's calm guide doesn't tell you to get rid of anger. It's a short guide to help the feeling pass without anyone getting hurt.",
  "calmGuideNotice": "**If you're in immediate danger**, please ask people around you for help or contact emergency services first, instead of staying on this app.",
  "calmGuideMomentTitle": "The moment anger rises",
  "calmGuideMomentBody1": "Anger can be a signal that something you care about has been violated. But in a strong anger state, judgment speeds up, and words and actions can become rougher than usual.",
  "calmGuideMomentBody2": "What's needed right now isn't to be **perfectly rational**, but to **delay your reaction by even 30 seconds**.",
  "calmGuideRoutineTitle": "60-second calm routine",
  "calmGuideStep1Title": "Stop",
  "calmGuideStep1Desc": "Pause replying, calling, commenting, or moving. Relax your hands and look away from the screen for a moment.",
  "calmGuideStep2Title": "Breathe",
  "calmGuideStep2Desc": "Inhale for 4 seconds, hold for 7, exhale for 8. It's okay if it isn't perfect.",
  "calmGuideStep3Title": "Check your body",
  "calmGuideStep3Desc": "Check whether your jaw, shoulders, fists, or stomach are tense, and release just one spot.",
  "calmGuideStep4Title": "Write it down",
  "calmGuideStep4Desc": "Even one sentence like \"Right now I'm angry because ___\" is enough.",
  "calmGuideBreathTitle": "4-7-8 breathing",
  "calmGuideBreathStep1": "Breathe in through your nose for 4 seconds.",
  "calmGuideBreathStep2": "Hold your breath for 7 seconds.",
  "calmGuideBreathStep3": "Slowly exhale through your mouth for 8 seconds.",
  "calmGuideBreathStep4": "Repeat 3 times if you can.",
  "calmGuideBreathNote": "If holding your breath that long is hard, shorten it to a comfortable count like **3-3-5**. What matters most is a slow, long exhale.",
  "calmGuideTimeoutTitle": "10-minute timeout",
  "calmGuideTimeoutBody": "The stronger the anger, the stronger the urge to resolve it right away. But talking now may bring out hurtful words first.",
  "calmGuideTimeoutExamplesTitle": "Example timeout phrases",
  "calmGuideTimeoutExample1": "\"I'm too angry right now, let's talk again in 10 minutes.\"",
  "calmGuideTimeoutExample2": "\"I'm pausing for a moment because I might say something hurtful.\"",
  "calmGuideTimeoutExample3": "\"I'm not running away, I just need to calm down before we talk again.\"",
  "calmGuideSensoryTitle": "Quick sensory grounding",
  "calmGuideSensory1Title": "Cold water",
  "calmGuideSensory1Desc": "Hold cold water on your wrists or face for about 10 seconds",
  "calmGuideSensory2Title": "Feel your feet",
  "calmGuideSensory2Desc": "Slowly notice the feeling of your feet touching the floor",
  "calmGuideSensory3Title": "Look around",
  "calmGuideSensory3Desc": "Quietly name 5 objects you can see",
  "calmGuideSensory4Title": "Drop your shoulders",
  "calmGuideSensory4Desc": "Exhale and lower your shoulders by just 1cm",
  "calmGuideQuestionsTitle": "Questions that help while writing",
  "calmGuideQuestion1": "What exactly made me angry?",
  "calmGuideQuestion2": "What did I expect but not receive?",
  "calmGuideQuestion3": "What action would I regret if I did it right now?",
  "calmGuideQuestion4": "What choice will tomorrow's me be grateful for?",
  "calmGuideTag1": "Emotion log",
  "calmGuideTag2": "Anger distancing",
  "calmGuideTag3": "Reminder check",
  "calmGuideDangerTitle": "Ask for help first in these cases",
  "calmGuideDanger1": "When the urge to hurt yourself or others feels strong",
  "calmGuideDanger2": "When the urge to throw or break things won't stop",
  "calmGuideDanger3": "When you feel like confronting or threatening the other person",
  "calmGuideDanger4": "When alcohol, drugs, or severe sleep deprivation make it hard to stay in control",
  "calmGuideDangerBody": "In these cases, don't try to get through it with the calm routine alone — ask people around you, professional services, or emergency services for help.",
  "calmGuideFooterTitle": "Fury Note Calm Guide",
  "calmGuideFooterDisclaimer": "This document does not replace medical diagnosis or treatment."
